03/08/2010
VLORA, Albania -- The Distribution System Operator (OSSH) has started to cut off electricity to about 500 businesses along the coast of Vlora due to unpaid debts, media reported Monday (August 2nd). 
Hotels, restaurants and bars have accumulated more than 150,000 euros in debt. 
Tourists fear that this could be the end of the season for the businesses. 
(Top Channel, Shekulli, Balkan Web, Top News - 02/08/10)
